It's a pretty good port, but has some optimisation issues which causes some lag despite my phone being pretty high end. The asset for a map in Chapter 4 is not properly loaded in, so first time players will be left a bit confused on that. The new content looks like they were machine translated too. Otherwise, this is a pretty decent port, the widescreen support is very nice, especially in trials. If you want a replay, or are getting into it first time, definitely give it a go, it's worth it!

It's fun. However, there's a few problems with the game that I've noticed while playing; none are game breaking, but one is very annoying. First, whenever someone tries to say something with a %, everything after it is cutoff. There are some visual glitches, such as with Jabberwock Park. And a big one I noticed recently is that there is no map when there is supposed to be one in Ch. 4. I might contact support, but they've never gotten back to me before; it seems pointless.

It's the most fun visual novel, action, murder mystery game I've ever played BUT I felt like I needed to address some issues: . 1) The game lags the most when exploring the island like, really bad ngl... Overall a very good port. Thanks for releasing V3 today!!

All in all not a bad game, but when my phone deleted the game I logged in only for it to write over my Google game data when I reconnected. Frustrating to lose all that progress, so I am walking away from this game.
Would be 5 star but you have to pay for the extra campaigns and everything in this game is pay pay pay.
Campaigns behind $8 pay wall per campaign... For a $5 total game imo.

It's...OK. very great design and concept on the tactical rpg style but after a while there is not that much to do. It's an Energy based game so once you run out you can't really progress any further, and the timer is fairly long to recover fully. With more development I would love to play this on a console with a decent storyline and bigger maps. Add in a little more character customization and your golden. Until then... meh
Nice grand N
Updated: game devs are very stingy and the rate of resource gain sucks. Gets very boring after awhile.

Low...very low character progression with very limited amount of resources. Story progression can get very hard after a single mission. The worst this is Tournaments, it says that the characters are capped at certain items and levels, but 50/50 enemy players can one shot with any of their characters as they were lelevs beyond you... don't know how this works and what im doing wrong, but tournament is a complete waste of time to wait insanely long for player to make a move, just to lose first tur
It's not fun when you up the difficulty and not give us anything in return. It's annoying. It basically stucks you up in a pay wall. The gameplay is ok. But the experience is too greedy.
Not worth it at this time. Great at the beginning, then gets paywalled unless you enjoy advancing at a snail's pace. Hopefully prices will lower, or they will tweak rewards.
Standard mobile game really, richest kid wins. So, if you have a massive disposable income I'm sure you'll have great fun. Otherwise, it gets really boring, really quickly...

Pretty good game just a little unstable. Few crashes and restarts along the way. Overall enjoying my time with this game. Well, until mission 37 when it falls of a cliff and you get slaughtered by scarab swarms every time. Thanks devs.

I must say once you get to approximately level 60, it becomes incredibly difficult up to that point it is incredibly easy. Most of my team is maxed out, I did this with out paying anything. but now my team will just get one shot within the first round. It's incredibly frustrating, as well even if you where to pay for the the things they just stop giving you to level up your caricatures attacks You may not get what you need You can't even use people from other factions you unlock. MONEY GRAB GAME

Pls can u make its single player campaign to b offline :0 ? Cuz not all pepol have load or wifi to enjoi le full game includin me and others :// If u make it offline for some single player features then others can try playing it faster without paying for load :^
Hit the grind wall at the end of the first campaign, no matter how much guild/salvage etc progress I make I have to shell out money. That's that.
It's a good game but , struggling to advance in the campaign need more resources as well as that I'm f2p and not able to pay that much to advance in chapters or purchase the next one
Not connected to internet is annoying
there's a bug that makes you stuck in a loop of chess whenever you do this event mission you can't go into your fights whatsoever please fix it now!!

Im experiencing an error after de beginning of the certus event, I go to the mission tab and a chest apear ready to open, only that when its done and show the total of the rewards again goes back to the chest ready to open, after 50 chest I restar the game but nothing change plz help

I liked this game at first but frankly it is too punishing for a free to play person. You quickly hit difficulty spikes that are decided by rng or just obscene damage scaling (scarabs). Normally you'd grind to get stronger but that is also punishing since they put timers around everything that could help you get stronger, 24 hr timers in most cases. It's a shameful way to try to force someone to pay money. Plus the drop rate for champion scrolls is stupid rare, hence keeping you weaker too.

The game is great right now. Early gifts and quick progression through the 1st campaign. Haven't hit a grind wall yet. Lots of events to give you some variety. Update: Found it! The game is a slow power-crawl for heroes and their varied upgrades. Lots of different types of fights, but you will be fighting the same fight 15 times a day to stay relevant (arena battles). Energy system can go die. Wish there was more/deeper strategy. Clans aren't useful. Not my type of game (repetitous) uninstalled.
Undisclosed pay to play and all bar one race is locked. Please disclose if your game is pay to play rather than listing it as free.
Stupidly expensive. You have to pay 10$ to buy a chance to get a low level gear. Incredibly stupid
The paywall shadows any skill you'd think this game could involve. A level to tough? Throw money at the game. Not very customisable, but I'll call it a dentist game if that means it's not very fun.
Would be great, but between enemy crits, enemy rez and the silly amount that they try and ask for money it's not worth it. Another game ruined by its own monitization

The amount of microtransactions in the game is insane, with very predatory timed "power up packs" to give an insane advantage. The pvp is incredibly unbalanced as well due to no matchmaking, the more money you're willing to part with the more you are guaranteed a win. Add it to the pile of extortionate warhammer mobile games. If you want a good warhammer turn based strategy, get Mechanicus instead. Its a full game for the same price as a single "power up pack".

Like another user here, I found the P2W jump... After playing for about a week, the jump in difficulty is ludicrous, particularly in the versus mode. Other players units doing over double my damage, and the only way to compete is to pay. Micro transactions aren't very "micro" either. Avoid

Have to drop the game to 2 stars since I finally ran into the point of not being able to play due to timegated energy/play tokens. If I want to play your game, let me. And sod off with your purchased energy microtransactions. For a name of Tacticus it surprisingly has fun tactical gameplay and team building, even though character upgrades do play a big part. For mobile standards it's one of the better Warhammer products.

Was a bit fun, but the game is way too pay to win and grindy. The cool down for most things is too long, the energy costs on campaigns are too high, and the amount of materials to upgrade the rank is absurdly high.

The game feels fun during the first three chapters of the starting campaign. But you hit a very, very obvious pay wall after that. The pacing slows down massively and You can't unlock additional campaigns unless you have 3 specific characters from those factions, which means you have to get lucky on the lootboxes.

Signs of mediocre development are plentiful by the 3rd "Boss" - playing the campaign. Another money grab, not supported by balanced gameplay or skilled developers. It plays like a little kid made it for sure. FAIL Uninstalled after about 1 month and 33$ Major disappointment.

Another of those 40K mobile games, unfortunately, and yet again it's another turn based game, too; On top of that, it's F2P! So we get the mandatory ridiculous amount of grinding and a bonkers energy system for battles that effectively last two? three minutes? Bah, how long until GW finally stops making the good stuff solely for WH: Fantasy and rid of poor 40K to have nothing but an array of mobile games? Majorkill done and fooled me with that sponsored review.

After a couple of entertaining hours you hit a Major paywall and can barely advance without buying (very expensive) stuff. I even bought a character for € 5, but it only got me a little further. The most annoying thing is the "energy" you consume for every game. You have to wait a long time until it recharges, or you pay for it. Really frustrating not being able to play.
*Not actually offline*

It was a fun pick up put down game. Until the 3rd stage of the base campaign. The swarms are unbeatable and good luck trying to beat a boss that drops 3+ swarms that can one shot all your heroes. Another Warhammer game in the bin, which is a bummer because Warhammer fans are starved for games as it is. 2 stars for the 2 playable stages.
It's fun for a bit but once you get to the later levels you pretty much have to spend money to progress massively pay to have any sort of reasonable advantage

Requested a profile transfer after I upgrade to a new device. Google play failed to automatically upload my primary account onto my new device. Contacted support team requesting help, and five days have past without any communication from them. Trying to fix this problem myself (I belive I can delete my new account, then access my primary account on the old device*, and have that uploaded in place on Google play). Doubtful I'll get a refund if I can't access my primary account again. 😑

Its a cool game in all based of the old fire raiders game with a 100 areas to spend money. Its completely a revenue oreneted. If your not spending money u dont get far. A minni campaign but pay for more and a useless side quests where u get junk.... Lol. Really id say not to bother if ur not looking to spend money. If you want to take a look at the mini campaign its the only thing good going for this game. Other then that screen after screen after screen of spees money. Its horrible To bad ...
starts out fun...actually starts out too easy all battle 3 stars, the bam dead..don't worry you can get past it...just pay some money and you can progress to next pay wall

Good simple fun with a nice dose of tactical small unit play. Plenty of in game purchase stuff, but (so far) able to progress just fine without touching it. EDIT: So editing this and dropping the rating. Found the P2W jump lol. Baddies suddenly got a lot harder while simultaneously upgrading my guys became exponentially harder. Clear point where I'm now being told I need to fork out $$ to continue. Uninstalling.

Gameplay is good and feels like a 40k game yes, but it feels very unfinished. Not enough characters, at all, missing most 40k factions, no Tau, no Kriegsman, only 2? Eldari. And each faction that is there only has 5 member, so they is no real customization yet.
You hit a noticeable difficulty spike a couple of hours in to insentivise buying packs. Alright gameplay but it's heavily geared towards micro transactions

Could be a great game.... but greedy lazy developers have set extortion prices in a game where you HAVE to summon characters to progress, but the only way to get summons after lvl 10 is spending money. You have to use raid tickets to get gear.... but you have to buy raid tickets with premium currency. The energy alotted to the player is too low, and energy refill is again, extortion. If you play, be ready to spend 100+ dollars to get to lvl 20.

Fix your game. Was having no issues for couple days since downloading and then out of no where cant do anything because some how game says I'm not connected to the internet, even though my phone is clearly connected to home wifi and it is saying I'm connected and not saying I'm having any connection issue or may not have internet. Edit: and if your response is I need to reinstall then I'm just deleting the game and not gonna bother with reinstalling it.
Just changed phones and all my progress didn't transfer across and help??

I was excited to try but it's been pretty boring so far. After half hour I don't really see much strategy or things to do really. I was hoping for an XCOM style experience though. Or at least some interesting multiplayer battles.

When I first tried the game I thought it was quite fun, despite the excess grinding that most free to play mobile games have. However even when following the pace of the game when it comes to the story and upgrade progress I notice the game has SEVERE balancing issues. Swarm enemies are the absolute worst, even when countering them with the rock, paper, scissors style combat. Boss enemies also do ludicrous amounts of damage to your heroes compared to numbers I see my heroes doing. Time wasting.

OK I originally gave the game 5 stars. But in the past couple weeks I have been having issues when I play. I constantly being stopped from playing because it's saying I'm not connected to wifi. I am connected. It's doesn't matter if I have full bars or not. Sometimes I can play a few games before itt says it and others I can't play at all. It sucks because I enjoy it when I can play it.

I was looking for something similar and I would rate it max 4 stars. 1 star was lossed due to annoying Bug where if you scroll to fast or too long all info disappears (it can be shop, hero list, missions) and only way to fix it is to restart game. It's annoying and it makes game seem cheap (even if it is) Another star was lost due to raid tokens. Lets be honest they are not user friendly and just a way for an extra cash grab. They shouldn't be included in this type of game.

While the game is very balanced, i have to say you guys have been having seriously bad signal during d tournament arena. I just lost 5 straight matches because i kept seeing no signal and d game was on with my opponent playing.

Well done games workshop for making another game pay to win. Cant progress with out paying for champions or blackstone. Would be alot higher stars because its a good game just paywall let it down. Awsome cash cow tho 👌

In the short term it's a ok game. I played it for a couple of weeks and deleted it. Game play is decent and graphics are fine. But I don't like the slow energy replenishment. I also don't like that your ability to farm is capped. Not my cup of tea.

Alright game..very grindy but doesn't let you just farm the levels without tokens they force you to pay for which sucks and definitely takes a star away but doesn't kill the game completely just puts a death clock on it as most people won't waste the time on the game. PvP is horrible. The maps are small and only specific champs are useful and if you go second you can win the game in one turn. Maps need to be double the size at least. The PvP costs the game 2 stars it's just that bad.
After the update i lost 9summons why is that..? Where is my summon go.pls look into it.. Thats why i give 2stars only

Not really very tactical. More like brute force. Basically if you have stronger units, you win. You get stronger units by buying packs or random drops. If this sounds familiar it's because literally every other game on here is the same, this one is Warhammer themed.. I've been playing a little more and it turns out there's no point in unlocking more characters as you can't really do anything with them. Massive pointless chore of a game.

Insanely grindy gacha that if you don't have great pulls its unplayable and they try and force you more than any other gacha I played to pay to unlock and upgrade character as you'll spend days just making your character just slightly stronger. The main issue is also its very stingy with energy as even watching ads and spending in game currency its a blink and you're outta energy situation.
Can't give this a 5 star ,they restrict your usage of characters in a team.

Honestly i cannot recommend this game simply because of the fact there is a lot of RNG involved in the fights despite being a strategy game (Think crits and a chance for units to resurrect). That in it's self is not terrible however losing costs full stamina. So you cannot test set up's or RNG can literally remove a paid resourse from you. If 90-100% of stamina was refunded on defeat i think i would be giving this a much higher score.
It's so boring playing with exact team in different modes. You are only free to use whatever in guild and arena... Fix that, that's not funny

Good game but keeps crashing during battle.1in3 battle's crash which means I can't advance in events or arena as you loose more places with 1 fail than you gain with 2 wins.glad iv not spent any money here.
lack luster and boring of all the types of games they could possibly make and this pos is what they put out?
Didnt make it past the tutorial, you need to be able to skip all that boring stuff or im just going to move on to another game, way too much handholding
The game has almost zero events. It becomes unplayable and grindy after a few days and it takes weeks to unlock new content.

Went in with some hope of innovation,unfortunately just another game that caters to the ultra rich disposable income crowd while the small spenders and f2p players are fed the illusion that they matter. It's fun at first, as was swgoh, msf, raid and all the others of the same genre, but as always you'll hit the pay walls within the early stages. Another greedy company too afraid to break the mould of a very, very tired genre. However, two stars for the gorgeous 3d models and gameplay execution.

Game is fun, it has really tugged at my 40k nostalgia. The rating could easily go up if the in game purchases (ie: items to progress your characters / weapons / play more levels in a day) were not so exorbitant. I don't mind shilling some cash at a game, I understand I am getting a (far from) "free" game, but this is nuts.
Fun till I got to 3rd boss, impossible to defeat.
Very limited content, lots of grinding and very repetitive with little to no rewards. Pay to play kind of game. Its good to pass time in waiting rooms.
The game was fun at first but after a while the levels become impossible without spending an obscene amount of money which I won't do on a game that essentially has very little actual content
Fun game but the devs could tone down the greed significantly. $40 for 3 units is not so much a "deal" and more of a cry for help.
Game is fun but but the daily energy is too limiting.
Changed my rating from 4 to 2 progression is slow monetization is almost required to get anything out of the game, great start but after a few weeks everything slows to a crawl

I love Warhammer 40k, but many issues with game. Making characters stronger is done in very small increments and doesn't feel impactful unless you pay. PvP is pay to win. Pricing in Canadian currency: bundles that give you three characters for $37, advertised at 70% off. What a joke. By opening 10 lootboxes at once you get guaranteed character. Requires 3000 shards. You buy 2600 shards for $28, 400 short. Game freezes, have to force close, and lose energy cost of starting mission.

I absolutely loved this game and put a lot of time into it, but when I had to replace my phone after it broke, I lost all of my progress as nothing was saved to Google play. Really demoralizes a passionate player. Especially when you can't log in and get your progress back before starting the tutorial.

Besides the smack in the face pay to win elements (pay to play too sadly unless you just get ungodly lucky with it's gacha system, as only one story mode of the game are you given what you need freely). It is and can be a fun game, but having played since release to now, some of the unnannounced changes have bugged me quite a bit. Including a provable drop rate decrease which has kneecapped my progression even while paying, just too greedy, 2/5

Issues with Onslaught mode. Was really enjoying this game but recently the Onslaught mode keeps crashing eveytime I try to use the Calandis character. Have lost 5 battle tokens now. Very frustrating in a game where you have limited opportunity to play missions and ruins enjoyment of the game.

I love the game play and model's The storyline is fun But character acquisition is ridiculously hard. To get drops it is incredibly difficult. My main problem is the prices in the store and insane for a big summon just 30$ I wouldn't mind spending my money on this game but, I want my money I spend here to get me characters Requisition drops are stupid hard to get, Either drop the prices or make Drops easier to get
Game routinely states that I'm not connected to the internet, when I am. As an example, i wouldnt be able to leave this review if I wasn't connected, yet the game thinks I am not connected.
CONFUSING-intresting

Slow and stingy. Absolutely not f2p and expensive at that. Everyone is just playing the same units and you have to get several hours of gameplay to get your first 10 pull. The are about 4 upgrade systems for each character and i can see that getting slow, grindy and expensive very fast. Add to that that epic or legendary characters looks absolutely hideously difficult and expensive to unlock. You should feel excited after your first 10 pull. My reaction was...is that is?

Pretty solid paywall blocking progress. Once your characters hit their XP caps and need their rarity increased, it's just grind or cash. After a week I still hadn't gathered the materials to improve even one character.

Fun strategy game, dialog in each break scene, haven't had to watch a video yet, but the in game purchases pop up a lot and are a bit high. Edit, lowered to 3 stars because while fun the lack of ability to play more regularly and requiring several hours between side missions is irritating, edit 2, seeing where previous users had issues with the game based on the necessity to buy things, the complete lack of in game currency at a decent price and the constant getting nothing you actually need.
Fun for a few days but it's all heavily front loaded. Stamina system is stingy. Hero upgrades are the same. Prices are pretty high for what little you get, outside full squad/campaign bundles.
1. Boring gameplay 2. Boring ultramarines

Played for a few hours and even more of a cash grab than this type of games usually is. Within minutes I was offered paid upgrade (to a game so simple I don't know why anyone would need it). Probably best avoided.
Why is this a game?

Forces you to use useless characters in campaign mode which is infuriating when you have a stable of better characters in the same faction you cant use. Microtransactions galore..More so than usual mobile games..It is a decent enough game..5.5 out of 10

Well it was fun while it lasted but just like every single game of its type you reach a certain point in campaign, pvp, raids etc where you don't have powerful enough characters so you either have GRIND the hell out of every previous mission or pay through nose for loot crates in the hopes of getting the right upgrade material. This game had high hopes but alas.

Seemed decent enough at first..... that is until it suddenly popped up that I didn't have the latest version. Tells me to download a 345mb update yet will not download a single byte. Stuck on zero percent. Nothing in app store either about an update. Will change review if it starts working

It's a good tactics game. However p2w is a BIG deal here. Anytime you unlock a character you are hit with "deal" to pay to get another copy of them. This is one of those your going to need multiple copies to make them stronger. Drop rates are terrible, go look. I get p2w is always a thing in gachas but the disparity between paid and f2p is TOO high..There needs to be less you can buy in this game. No deals after every character unlock, and lower the price of 10 pulls to 2500.
The sheer number of pop up ads made me uninstall after 10 minutes

Decent game, has some fun aspects but you have to grind or pay to be able to continue the campaign. The worst part of the game is the fact that you have to have "Raid Tickets" to quickly replay any level you have already beaten with 3 stars, but the part that makes it worse is there is only a certain number of times you can raid a level! Why make players use RAID TICKETS if you're already limited in the number of times you can play a level every day?! Just make the raids free!!!
Very limiting experience. Game throws you a deal that's 70% off. Sounds great right? Well it's still $30. Horrible.

Didn't even know what was going on. Love the 40k universe but within the first 5 minutes I was already confused. Game play is too fast you don't even get to see the animations. There's alot of typos which to me shows that this game was rushed and not looked over.

In spite of the name, it's not about tactics, it's about numbers. Did you pay to have high numbers that are skinned as 40k? Tough luck. It results in your chaos terminator not even being able to kill a single imperial guardsman. Because again: Tactics don't matter. Cash matters.

Great game a tad too grindy, and forces you to buy when you reach a certain spot in game. For most South-africans cant afford your high prices. Not everyone can afford dollars, and ya needa be stomped fo dat, ya greedy gits. We get paid in Rand, not dollar. So try accomidating others with your prices

Starts strong and quickly falls off. When you start you get great units. Gameplay is absolutely amazing and insanely addictive and fun. Eventually however you are going to slow down. And once you do this is where problems start. In order to advance your units you need more items, tokens, equipment. In order to obtain what you need you have to auto clear levels. However that's exactly when you run out of raid tokens. And that's when game becomes horrible and boring. And I actually spent money...
This is a good game but after the 4th chapter of the first campaign it is highly pay motivated unless you want it to take days just to pass 1 stage
Fun for a bit then got bored. f2p is basically impossible unless you grind for weeks and don't mind not progressing and getting slaughtered by whales. Gacha at its finest.
Loads of freezes an crashes. But it consumes your scrap run tries...worked fine till 3 days ago. Now...uninstalled.
Gameplay is good, although can feel a little too easy at times. First campaign is good, but the paywall for the other 2 is extortion. £25 each is not a price anyone should pay for a mobile game
After some level impossible to Windows a battle without paying
Enjoyable, but I can't rate it higher unless YOU BALANCE THE NECRON SWARMS DAMAGE !!!
The whole energy and battle tokens system is so horrendously terrible. You need to wait upp to 5 hours to get a single try in onslaught and salvage run.

A lot of fun so far however. Having issues with a couple purchases and haven't heard a peep from the studio yet. I like to spend, I can spend. I won't if I can't get service in a reasonable time frame. Purchases don't show details beyond chests of black crystal. Just says the size.
The server connection drops randomly a lot after the Eldari update. Fix ASAP

Grindy. Fork up some money? The game play is repetitive but still satisfying for a win. The mechanics have so many subtle nuances that require you to engage in many fascets, but is exciting, but laborious. The grind is real. And you'll experience stagnation after basically a weekend because you need some magical spoon or whatever to progress but the only way to acquire this item is through a daily "drop" or to purchase your own "drop". Hmmm.... No lore. Cash grab. Fun for a weekend.
Too much going on,....serious battery draining.

Same old mobile game story. Advertised as free, uses sinister psychology to lure players in, then turns into gambling. In its defense, the game is as pretty as the adverts make it look. Very rare honesty in the cesspit of social media marketing. Fast progress initially, big numbers and lots of button press training pre-lvl40. It also asks for a review during this period... THEN you realise your team can't progress without spending a fortune, gambling with loot crates, or grinding forever.
Micro transactions is the name of the game!
Is good up until the alpha null battle he too op and can just heal himself most of the damage and the nearly 1hit kill every base character so clearly becomes pay to win I'm out
Just starting out. The gameplay is fun. The pvp is pay to win though.

My main concern and reasoning for the 2 star review is I'm having extreme battery drain while playing which makes me almost not want to continue playing which is sad because I have liked the gameplay so far.

As with most f2p mobile gave it begins showering you with progress, then presents the "wall" at which units are simply too weak to progress. Then it is down to tedious grinding repetitions of whichever missions *might* drop things. It's dressed up as a tactics game, but it's really just stacking numbers. The influence your Tactical choices make is very minimal. Expect to be mildly entertained for 2 hours, then dumped into tedium and microtxn harassment.
In the grim darkness of the far future there is only paywall. And wow do you run into that paywall quickly!

The gameplay, at its core, is fun and has a lot of potential but: The badly designed gamemodes and poor AI really ruin how deep and interesting the game could be, 1v1 PvP is really fun but only happens once in a while as part of an event. Progressiom and pricing is absurd, F2P progression is abysmal and completely based around RNG so you can't even farm characters you like. P2W progression is.. expensive, characters cost 10-20€ to unlock without any upgrades, expect to pay thousands for upgrad

A great distraction for a week or two. Unless you're willing to spend money to speed up your progress you're basically farming for weeks for a chance to unlock something new, which from f2p perspective makes playing the game a slog. The battles themselves end up feeling like there's very little strategy involved in plays since you usually end up fighting opponents that are either a lot weaker or considerably stronger than you.
replyContent: Hmm...I wonder if there isn't something off with your version. We do have some popups -- we have to make a living and fund future development -- but what you describe is really excessive; you shouldn't be seeing popups after each battle/mode. More like once, twice per session, tops. Please update and try again?

content: After latest update I cant play at all. After half a day you hit a huge psy wall. Pay to win move over, pay to play. What a letdown for 40k

I played this for about a week. It became painfully clear that the game forces you into purchasing loot boxes to try to get a specific item that doesn't drop anywhere else in order to level your units. This isn't the worst crime, however. The worst is that the game just isn't very fun. All grind and no substance. I gave 2 stars since there is some good graphic design that deserves at least a nod. Hard pass.
Fun part as tactical but so pay to win that it's not fun and the bundles cost more than some full games would cost.
Absolutely love the game but the drop rates are incredibly low to get the characters to move onto other chapters so dropped my rating sue to that reason only

Not sure if I did not play long enough or what, but I did not enjoy the game because I did not want to play a space marine, and if I did want to play a space marine it wouldn't be the ultra marines. I'd be more interested in a game like this if I could be a Necron or Tyranid. And if you can play as one of those races then it should be right from the get go and not force you to play marines for hours before you unlock the content you want.

Another pay to win game, PvP is way unbalanced you face players that have bought every thing possible. Leveling up characters to complete campaign is not possible unless you face other people in arenas. Games just how I thought it would end up and I pre-registered for this game.

Good game so far a few issues tho. After you reach certain level you run out of tokens and I literally cannot play any game modes at all and have to wait forever for energy and tokens to recharge so have nothing to do so Please decrease the wait time to get boss raid tokens and other modes tokens as it's far too long a wait with nothing to do bar one campaign mission every ten mins or so. Maybe add some sort of free play game mode? That doesn't require energy or tokens?

Ok for a gacha game, but Snowprint doesn't do a great job vetting their advertisers and shows ads for State of Survival: Zombie War which hijacks the app and has no way to exit the ad without installing State of Survival: Zombie War or force closing Tacticus. The same problem exists in Rivengard which is another Snowprint game that was cloned and rebranded to create Tacticus.

I would recommend waiting for this game to get some significant content updates I played the first day for a few hours and since then, within 10 mins, there's nothing to do and the things that are there to do are just the same things over and over again. It's a good concept (although not original) and the character development system is identical to others that I have played so nothing original here either. The only thing I can really praise this for is the lack of ads.

Revision. To their credit the support team responded to try to help me recover my account so for a helpful support they get 2 stars. Luckily this has given me time to realize that this game and its aggressive microtransactions are not for me. Original review: So I had all my data and progress completely wiped the same day as I spent $100 on the monetization in this game. I don't think I need to explain why I give it 1 star.

Its generic and simple, same as any similar battle game with 40k theme tacked on. And even that is done by someone who doesnt know what grimdark is... Art is cartoony and bright colors. Not very 40k. Nothing new or exciting, pass...
Good fundamental stratagem game. Too many in app purchases. Pay to win.

This game definitely doesn't give you much for your money. I like the game but it's a money pit. I'm thinking about leaving this game along with my people. I'm going to give it another week before I publish my review on a few platforms. This game has the potential to be great but the greed is already in the forefront.

The rng is bad, from trying to power up your artifacts, getting good artifacts, to just getting a character you want. The positive being there is a pity system but you potentially have to spend 180 wishes (approx. $450) to get the character you want Lastly is the lack of character roadmaps and time to prepare for upcoming characters.

No controller option. It is obvious that an enormous amount of work went into developing this game which makes it all the more frustrating that there is no controller option. content: Everything's changed, from easy to medium level of game difficulty is enough for 70% new to late players but now became imbalance. It is now hard-very hard-extreme hard-impossible to win hard on almost every mode(Abyss/Superstring, Memorial Bosses, Elysian Realm, Blockade etc). Some things that are worthless also can be earned in-game are being sold expensively. In the past, I gacha-ed until bankrupt for only 1 weapon and 3 stigmas, doesn't make me super strong at all, became useless after few updates. Stigma and weapon upgrade materials are unnecessarily sold expensively, exchanging in the shop requires a lot of materials. Earning is slow and used up pretty fast. When I want to craft weapons and stigmas, it feels sad...because it may take a year or two to craft only 1 stigma, or even none. It needs tons of "Ether fuel" ranging somewhere from 700 to 1100 mixing with other materials, the same for weapon crafting materials, must play a lot of co-ops and daily limited material-gathering stage until you are tremendously bored, tired and gave up on it. Surely doesn't make any sense, not only they rip off our cash, but still wanna make the game so hard and unplayable. Every time they found something we can earn/exchange fast, they nerf it...forcing us to earn slower even for useless stuff. Modes that are playable and medium balance-ness such as the new elysian realm released not long ago, now broken, you either die fast or fight undying enemies until the countdown reaches 0 then lose.
